Reasoning: The paper discusses steganography techniques in multimedia data, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). It also mentions the use of steganography in military and medical fields, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of images for reversible data hiding, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The techniques mentioned in the paper involve manipulating data, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
